      "id": 56375,
      "kuerzel": "LOSCM",
      "bezeichnung": "Logistics and Supply Chain Management",
      "lernziele": "<p><strong>Professional skills</strong></p>\n<p>Participants will be able to:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Explain the principles of Supply Chain Management (SCM) and know about its levers to business success</li>\n<li>Apply concepts to balance demand and supply, meet customer service objectives and minimize total supply chain cost.</li>\n<li>Evaluate value chain processes and define appropriate KPI for measurements and improvements</li>\n<li>Master the most important information flows</li>\n<li>Perform typical tasks of procurement, logistic management and supplier management</li>\n<li>Understand the basic planning processes for distribution networks and facilities&nbsp;</li>\n</ul>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong>Methodological skills</strong></p>\n<p>Participants will be able to:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Analyse industrial value-adding processes by selecting and using the right methods</li>\n<li>Systematically identify potential for improvement and derive measures and recommendations.</li>\n</ul>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong>Personal skills</strong></p>\n<p>Participants will be able to:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Realistically plan their own personal time and keep to the schedule when solving complex case studies and exercises.</li>\n<li>Position themselves in terms of their attitude towards sustainable decisions in the supply chain.</li>\n</ul>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong>Social skills</strong></p>\n<p>Participants will be able to:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Realistically plan and divide tasks based on the workload in complex case studies as a team</li>\n<li>Solve conflicts within the team&nbsp;</li>\n</ul>",
      "planinhalt": "<ul>\n<li>Warehouse Management: Layout, Equipment, Material Flows, Processes (such as Order-Picking)</li>\n<li>Transportation Management: Shipment Characteristics, Transportation Modes, Partnerships &amp; Network aspects</li>\n<li>Inventory Planning and Optimization: Decoupling Point, Inventory Cost, Service Level, Dealing with Uncertainty</li>\n<li>Purchasing: Sourcing Decisions, Cost Calculation, Negotiation</li>\n<li>Business Dimension of SCM: Make or Buy-Decisions, Tradeoffs and TCO-Considerations</li>\n<li>Supply Chain Strategy: Put SC-decisions into the overall context of the organizational goals</li>\n</ul>",
      "bibliographie": "<pre id=\"tw-target-text\" class=\"tw-data-text tw-text-large XcVN5d tw-ta\" dir=\"ltr\" data-placeholder=\"&Uuml;bersetzung\"></pre>\n<p><strong>Required literature, scripts, books:</strong></p>\n<pre id=\"tw-target-text\" class=\"tw-data-text tw-text-large XcVN5d tw-ta\" dir=\"ltr\" data-placeholder=\"&Uuml;bersetzung\"></pre>\n<ul>\n<li>All Materials used in Lecture and Exercises</li>\n</ul>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong>Further reading (recommendation to students):</strong></p>\n<ul>\n<li>Will be advised during the course</li>\n</ul>\n<pre id=\"tw-target-text\" class=\"tw-data-text tw-text-large XcVN5d tw-ta\" dir=\"ltr\" data-placeholder=\"&Uuml;bersetzung\"><span class=\"Y2IQFc\" lang=\"en\"><br /><br /></span></pre>",
